-- Muralitharan Takes 5-63 to Close on 800-Wicket Mark in Final Cricket Test
-- Dan Baynes
-- 2010-07-21T07:57:42Z
-- http://www.bloomberg.com/news/2010-07-21/muralitharan-takes-5-63-to-close-on-800-wicket-mark-in-final-cricket-test.html

          
          
             Sri Lanka spinner Muttiah
Muralitharan lifted his record tally of Test wickets to 797 in
his final match before quitting cricketâ€™s elite format.   
 Needing eight wickets to become the first bowler to reach
the 800 mark, Muralitharan took 5-63 to help bowl out India for
276 on day four of the series-opening match in Galle.   
 Sri Lanka enforced the follow-on after making 520-8
declared in its first innings, meaning India will go straight
back out to bat in its second innings.  
          
          


  


        